<subSubSection pageId="12" pageNumber="13" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="12.[151,1437,259,1229]" pageId="12" pageNumber="13">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,315,1133,1157]" pageId="12" pageNumber="13">Remarks.</emphasis>
This new species is distinguished from its congeners by its characteristic thoracic coloration. Also, it differs from 
<taxonomicName box="[314,607,1168,1192]" class="Insecta" family="Clusiidae" genus="Sobarocephala" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="12" pageNumber="13" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="vockerothi">
<emphasis box="[314,607,1168,1192]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="13">Sobarocephala vockerothi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in the characters stated in the key.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection box="[199,1116,1204,1229]" pageId="12" pageNumber="13" type="etymology">
<paragraph blockId="12.[151,1437,259,1229]" box="[199,1116,1204,1229]" pageId="12" pageNumber="13">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,334,1205,1229]" pageId="12" pageNumber="13">Etymology.</emphasis>
The specific name refers to the large surstylus (Greek: 
<emphasis box="[955,1026,1205,1228]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="13">megas</emphasis>
+ 
<emphasis box="[1042,1099,1204,1228]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="13">stylis</emphasis>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
